Implemented the thermal chamber hysteresis controller in:

- `components/controller/controller.c`

Added visible self-tests in:

- `agent_tests/test_controller_behavior.py`

What changed:
- Boot-safe heater-off initialization
- Proper banded hysteresis behavior:
  - `<47` → `HEATING` / heater on
  - `>52` → `SAFE_OFF` / heater off
  - `47..49` → `HOLDING` / preserve actuator state
  - `50..52` rising → early heater off in `HOLDING`
  - `50..52` not rising → preserve actuator state in `HOLDING`
- Fail-safe off on:
  - malformed input
  - explicit sensor timeout
  - stale valid sensor gap `>1000 ms`
- No false timeout on ordinary one-step sensor gaps

